&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Knowledge Required&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Client Scripts and UI Policies&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Review wiki documentation for Client Scripts and UI Policies&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Test Case&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Refer to &lt;strong&gt;Task #19.&lt;/strong&gt; The client discovered that when Confidential incident is being created by itil role holder who is not &amp;#34;security_officer&amp;#34; the user may accidentally tick &amp;#34;Confidential&amp;#34; flag and save incident without setting anyone as &amp;#34;Assigned To&amp;#34;. Thus the incident may become invisible for him and only &amp;#34;security_officer&amp;#34; will be able to see it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;Customer wants to double check that SOMEBODY is specified in &amp;#34;Assigned To&amp;#34; before &amp;#34;Confidential&amp;#34; incident is saved. Also if  IT user without security_officer role who ticked &amp;#34;Confidential&amp;#34; is not specified in &amp;#34;Assigned To&amp;#34; then a warning should be displayed &amp;#34;You have set incident to Confidential but you are not specified in Assigned To. If you save your incident then it will become invisible for you.&amp;#34; and &lt;/span&gt;incident&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt; submission (or save) should be prohibited.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trainee  Instructions&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Trainee should propose the technical design and get approval from Coach before implementing the solution. After approval please implement it in the instance specified by the Coach using separate update set. Perform the unit testing before reporting task as completed to the Coach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
